sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant XTerm as xterm.js<br/>(TerminalView)
    participant Hook as useTerminal
    participant Bridge as tauri-bridge
    participant TCmd as commands/terminal.rs
    participant PTY as ports/pty.rs<br/>(PtyHandle)
    participant Shell as Shell Process

    Hook->>Bridge: createTerminalSession()
    Bridge->>TCmd: invoke("create_terminal_session")
    TCmd->>PTY: PtyHandle::spawn(shell, cwd, 24, 80)
    PTY->>Shell: Fork + exec shell
    TCmd->>TCmd: Store handle in SessionMap
    TCmd->>TCmd: Spawn pty_read_loop thread
    TCmd-->>Bridge: { session_id }
    Bridge-->>Hook: session_id
    Hook->>Hook: Register onData, onResize listeners

    loop User Interaction
        User->>XTerm: Keystroke
        XTerm->>Hook: terminal.onData(data)
        Hook->>Bridge: writeToPty(session_id, bytes)
        Bridge->>TCmd: invoke("write_to_pty")
        TCmd->>PTY: handle.write(data)
        PTY->>Shell: Write to PTY master

        Shell->>PTY: Output to PTY slave
        PTY->>TCmd: pty_read_loop: reader.read_chunk(buf)
        TCmd->>XTerm: emit("pty:data", {session_id, data})
        XTerm->>XTerm: terminal.write(text)
    end

    Note over User,Shell: Window resize triggers fitAddon.fit()
    XTerm->>Hook: terminal.onResize({cols, rows})
    Hook->>Bridge: resizePty(session_id, rows, cols)
    Bridge->>TCmd: invoke("resize_pty")
    TCmd->>PTY: handle.resize(rows, cols)
